The paper discusses optimization in generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper analyzes the gradient descent form of GAN optimization, which is a common optimization technique used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
